  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Start by washing the strawberries in water and removing the stalk and leaves from the strawberry, by twisting or carefully using a knife. Finely chop the stalks and leaves, they’re totally edible!"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the strawberries thin and pop them into a mixing bowl, sprinkle over the sugar, gently mix through then set to one side. Tear in some basil leaves and tip in the balsamic vinegar. Mix to combine."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In another bowl, whisk the double cream, icing sugar and vanilla essence until forming stiff peaks, soften the cream cheese in another bowl then gently mix together."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now you are ready to build your mini cheesecakes, pipe or spoon the cheesecake base onto a cracker leaving a well for the strawberries to sit in. Spoon in the strawberries and some of their juice."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For a fancy garnish, top with extra some fresh basil and a little lick of the strawberry syrup."
    }
  ],
